WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.125
Developing conflict-agility means utilizing effective communication strategies to reduce strife

00:00:05.125 --> 00:00:10.250
while harnessing conflict to improve outcomes. The Claim-Support-Question protocol is

00:00:10.250 --> 00:00:15.375
highly useful here. When a solution is proposed, stating the

00:00:15.375 --> 00:00:20.500
claim, providing evidence, and articulating provoked questions treats explanations as

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:25.625
thinking events. There are five main strategies for resolving conflicts:

00:00:25.625 --> 00:00:30.751
Collaboration, Accommodation, Competition, Compromising, and Avoidance. Let us try a

00:00:30.751 --> 00:00:35.876
short prediction. If there is an immediate safety emergency that

00:00:35.876 --> 00:00:41.001
requires a swift decision, which strategy should be used? Collaboration

00:00:41.001 --> 00:00:46.126
or Competition? The correct answer is Competition, or forcing, because

00:00:46.126 --> 00:00:51.251
the emergency must be resolved instantly. Selecting the right strategy

00:00:51.251 --> 00:00:56.376
for the context shows excellent effort in mastering conflict-agility.
